  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into <strong>chunky chips</strong>, then add them to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over <strong>half</strong> the <strong>dried sage</strong> (save the rest for later!) and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 30 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-christmas-vegan-burger/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Trim the <strong>Brussels sprouts</strong> and chop them in half, then add them to a<strong> food processor</strong> and blitz for 30 secs or until finely shredded</p><p>Tip: Don't have a food processor? Slice them finely instead!</p><p>Add the<strong> shredded sprouts</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over them until bright green and wilted, then set aside to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-christmas-vegan-burger/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>baby button mushrooms</strong> finely</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced mushrooms</strong> with the <strong>smoked paprika</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until softened – these are your<strong> 'bacon' mushrooms</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-christmas-vegan-burger/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> 'bacon' mushrooms</strong>, <strong>wilted sprouts</strong>, <strong>mayo</strong> and <strong>mustard ketchup</strong> to a large bowl</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up until fully combined – this is your <strong>sprout slaw</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-christmas-vegan-burger/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>Line a baking tray with <strong>baking paper</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>ultimate vegan burger patties</strong> to the tray and put the tray in the oven for 10-12 min or until cooked through</p><p>Whilst the patties are cooking, the<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-christmas-vegan-burger/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]<strong> </span>olive oil</strong> to a pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs until a sandy paste has formed</p><p>Add the <strong>vegetable stock </strong>with the<strong> Marmite</strong> and<strong> </strong>remaining<strong> dried sage </strong>and cook for 4-5 min, stirring occasionally, until thickened to a gravy-like consistency – this is your <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-christmas-vegan-burger/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the patties are cooked, remove the tray from the oven and top each patty with a <strong>cheese flavour slice </strong>–<strong> </strong>these are your<strong> cheesy vegan patties</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> brioche buns </strong>to the other side of the tray</p><p>Return the tray to the oven<strong> </strong>for 3-4 min or until the cheese has melted and the brioche is warmed through</p><p>Cut the <strong>warmed brioche buns</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-christmas-vegan-burger/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Fill each <strong>brioche bun</strong> with a <strong>cheesy</strong> <strong>vegan patty </strong>and a spoonful of <strong>sprout slaw</strong></p><p>Serve any remaining<strong> slaw</strong> to the side with the <strong>chunky chips</strong> and <strong>gravy</strong> for dipping</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
